{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01YS8YTF8fCeWzDtzWyVSVT9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `ray-head` service exposes ports 6379 and 8265. Port 6379 is the GCS (Global Control Store) port. Port 8265 is the Ray dashboard.\n\nThe issue is that `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` doesn't work for connecting from an external client pod. That address format is for when you're running ON the Ray cluster nodes.\n\nFor a Ray 2.9.0 cluster, to connect from a client that's not part of the cluster, you should use:\n- `ray://ray-head:10001` for the Ray Client protocol, but that port isn't exposed by the service\n- Or submit the job directly to the head node where `address=\"auto\"` works\n\nSince the service only exposes 6379 and 8265, I need to figure out how to properly connect using the GCS port directly.\n\nUsing `ray.init(address=\"ray-head:6379\")` should work in older Ray versions if the session files are available locally, but I need to check how Ray is actually initialized on the head pod to understand what's required.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":504,"cache_read_input_tokens":33745,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":504},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2e47e4dd-d90f-4e8f-b56e-8b5d473a52e8","uuid":"86dac94b-0ab9-494f-8ef0-adc4fdb8e519","request_id":"req_011CcQ4Z9u54Q8x9nKuvDXut"}
